-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, New World Resources Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-09T14:57:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-new-world-resources-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 0.9 percent to 908.40 at the close of trading in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of  Austria  fell 5.5 percent
to 378 koruna, its biggest retreat in five months. The stock
tumbled 7.1 percent in Vienna, its home market, on July 5 and
July 6, when the Czech market was closed for public holiday.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, dropped 0.5 percent to 104.5 koruna, snapping a
four-day gain.  Europe ’s benchmark coal futures contracts fell
0.5 percent to $97 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
